<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-18T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-18T10:00:00-05:00" n="810" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d810">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111 A.R./1092: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Nicholson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-18T09:00:00-06:00">May 18,
                                    1940—9 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 12:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>46. Department’s telegram No. 31, May 17, 7 p.m. Nicaraguan Minister for
                            Foreign Affairs confirms that affirmative reply regarding Uruguayan
                            proposal was sent by telegraph to Panama on May 16.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Nicholson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>